## Setup

```bash
source .venv/bin/activate
make install
make test
```

## Quick start

```bash
# Run the example task to verify everything works (~30 seconds)
make preprocess PREPROCESS_ARGS="task=example"
make train TRAIN_ARGS="task=example training.epochs=5"
make eval EVAL_ARGS="task=example"

# Then create your own task (copy the example as a starting point)
cp experiments/tasks/example.py experiments/tasks/my_task.py
# Edit my_task.py, then run with: make train TRAIN_ARGS="task=my_task"
```

## Project structure

```
src/{{ project_slug }}/                    experiments/
(library — pip install)                (pipeline — not distributed)
─────────────────────                  ────────────────────────────
models/                                tasks/
  └── your model architectures           └── example.py (copy as starting point)
data/                                        ├── preprocess()
  └── datasets, transforms, collators       ├── build_dataloader()
utils.py                                    ├── build_model()
                                             ├── make_compute_loss()
                                             ├── make_evaluate()
                                             └── make_test_evaluate()
                                       train.py (dispatcher)
                                       trainer.py (Accelerate, checkpoints, logging)
                                       eval.py (checkpoint loading, fold aggregation)
                                       preprocess.py (config hashing, skip-if-exists)

configs/config.yaml                    Makefile (all commands)
configs/experiment/*.yaml              scripts/slurm/ (job submission)
```

## Common commands

```bash
# Local
make train TRAIN_ARGS="training.lr=0.01"
make train TRAIN_ARGS="+experiment=my_experiment"

# Cluster
make submit                              # sync + submit to {{ default_tier }}-VRAM tier
make submit TIER=high                    # high-VRAM GPUs
make sweep SWEEP="training.lr=0.001,0.01,0.1"
make status                              # check jobs
make logs                                # tail latest output
```

